	(197, 1, '2015-03-05 03:03:13', '2015-03-05 03:03:13', '<body id="other" class="page page-id-13 page-parent page-template page-template-page-about-php win8.1 chrome chrome-0">\r\n		<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-faq.jpg&#39;);">\r\n            <header>\r\n                <h1>About the Quality of Life Measures</h1>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n       	</section>\r\n        <div class="row">\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n                <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                    <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                        <h2>About the Project</h2>\r\n                        <hr>\r\n                    </header>\r\n                    <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                        <p>What is wellbeing?</p>\r\n                        <p>Throughout human history, philosophers, poets, theologians, and scholars have sought the answer to that seemingly simple question. From King Solomon to the city squares of ancient Greece to worldwide internet debates, humanity has discussed just what the good life might meanand how to help more people achieve that.</p>\r\n                        <a class="btn flat gray " href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/the-concepts/#about_the_project">Learn More</a>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n                <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                    <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                        <h2>Advisory Board</h2>\r\n                        <hr>\r\n                    </header>\r\n                    <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                        <p>The Baugh Centers advisory board is comprised of a diverse group of scholars, entrepreneurs, thought leaders and involved citizens who bring a variety of perspectives to the table. Their feedback is critical to fostering an informed and thoughtful dialogue on quality of life. Advisory Board members provide guidance for continuous improvement of our project.</p>\r\n                        <a class="btn flat gray " href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/contributors">Learn More</a>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </section>\r\n            <section class="post standard">\r\n                <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                    <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                        <h2>Our Contributors</h2>\r\n                        <hr>\r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                        <p>The Quality of Life Measures Advisory Board is comprised of a diverse group of esteemed scholars, business leaders, and thought leaders who bring a variety of perspectives to the project. These experts and their feedback are critical to efforts to foster an informed and thoughtful dialogue on project. Advisory Board members provide strategic guidance for continuous improvement in the quality and value of the projects research.</p>\r\n                        <a class="btn flat gray jump" href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/contributors">Meet our Contributors</a>\r\n                    </article>\r\n                </div>\r\n            </section>\r\n        </div>', 'About', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'about', '', '', '2016-02-11 20:09:38', '2016-02-11 20:09:38', '', 0, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/?page_id=197', 0, 'page', '', 0),
	(199, 1, '2015-03-05 03:03:26', '2015-03-05 03:03:26', '<body id="other" class="page page-id-33 page-child parent-pageid-13 page-template page-template-page-about-the-initiative-php win8.1 chrome chrome-0">\r\n	<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-aboutinit.jpg&#39;);">\r\n                <header>\r\n                    <h1>Quality of Life Measures?</h1>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                </header>\r\n            </section>\r\n            <div class="row">\r\n                <section class="post standard">\r\n                    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                        <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <h2>The Concepts of WellBeing and Quality of Life</h2>\r\n                            <hr>\r\n                            <p style="margin-top:200px;"><span style="color:green; font-style:italic;">Quality of life can be examined by looking at overall subjective wellbeingthe sum of happiness and life satisfaction. The former represents pleasant emotions and feelings of joy  and the later refers to a person\'s reflection of his or her life as a whole.</span></p>\r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <p>Though the concepts have gone by other names and held different definitions, quality of life and human wellbeing have been a leading focus of scholarly, philosophical, and religious thought for much of human history. The great philosophers believed that wellbeing meant virtuous living. With the Enlightenment came the notion that absolute happiness could be achieved through human intervention in societys established structuresthat it was possible, in effect, to create a heaven on earth, as shown by the French revolutions and the various social experiments that followed.</p>\r\n                            <p>With the rise of this notion, societal goals that had previously belonged to the informal realm of societyeconomic development; advancement of human capabilities, freedom and creativity; environmental sustainability; fairness; and social justicenow became core governmental objectives. Although the items mentioned above are important aspects of a good society, people of different philosophical, religious, cultural, and political opinions disagree as to their relative importance for quality of life.</p>\r\n                            <p>The Baugh Center at Baylor University is launching this new, empirically based project because accurate measurements are indispensable for making decisions about how best to create a society with a high quality of life. When defined carefully, quality of life and wellbeing are holistic concepts that can be measured in a relatively precise manner and in objective, cross-cultural terms.</p>\r\n                            <p>Together with many professionals in the wellbeing field, The Baugh Center considers wellbeing as a combination of two underlying components. The first is the more short-term and pleasant emotions and feelings of joy that a person experiences at any given time, and the second is a persons cognitive, evaluative reflection of his or her life as a whole. The former is more closely aligned with what people today refer to as happiness and the latter is what scholars refer to as life satisfaction.</p>\r\n                        </article>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n                <section class="post standard">\r\n                    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                        <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <h2 id="about_the_project">About the Project</h2>\r\n                            <hr>\r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <p>What is quality of life?</p>\r\n                            <p>Throughout human history, philosophers, poets, theologians, and scholars have sought the answer to that seemingly simple question. From King Solomon to the city squares of ancient Greece to worldwide internet debates, humanity has discussed just what the good life might meanand how to help more people achieve that.</p>\r\n                            <p>The Baugh Center seeks to further this conversation as it continues into the 21st century. Through research, education, and discussion, we aim to advance understanding of how individual quality of life intersects with society as a whole;how to comprehend and measure the various aspects of wellbeing and quality of life;and how to inspire people to improve lives in their communities and society at large.</p>\r\n                            <p>As part of this goal, we have produced measures of quality of life for all 50 U.S. states and more than 140 countries. These measures open new doors for research and form the core of our efforts to improve quality of life. The measures focus on six societal dimensions of human wellbeing: Community & Relationships, Health & Environment, Freedom, Living Standard, Opportunity, and Peace & Security.</p>\r\n                        </article>\r\n\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n            </div>', 'The Concepts', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-concepts', '', '', '2016-02-12 07:18:14', '2016-02-12 07:18:14', '', 0, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/?page_id=199', 0, 'page', '', 0),
	(201, 1, '2015-03-05 03:03:57', '2015-03-05 03:03:57', '<body id="other" class="page page-id-39 page-child parent-pageid-13 page-template-default win8.1 chrome chrome-0">\r\n<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-advisory.jpg&#39;);">\r\n                <header>\r\n                    <h1>Introducing our Contributors</h1>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                </header>\r\n            </section>\r\n            <div id="content" class="row">\r\n                <section class="post standard">\r\n                    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                        <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <h2>Advisory Board</h2>\r\n                            <hr>\r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <p>The Baugh Centers advisory board is comprised of a diverse group of scholars, entrepreneurs, thought leaders and involved citizens who bring a variety of perspectives to the table. Their feedback is critical to fostering an informed and thoughtful dialogue on quality of life. Advisory Board members provide guidance for continuous improvement of our project.</p>\r\n                            <p>The role of the Advisory Board is to further the study and measurement of wellbeing and provide insight based on current discussions in economics, sociology, psychology, and other disciplines. All Advisory Board members review the Quality of Life Measures, offering feedback to further improve the methodology, data sets, and analysis.</p>\r\n                            <p>In the spirit of the dialogue that accompanies this ever-developing field of work, each member of the board may not endorse every data interpretation or methodological choice. Such challenges serve to support the essence of the initiative by fostering rich and transparent discussion on the subjects examined.</p>\r\n                        </article>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n                <section class="post standard">\r\n                    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                        <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <h2>Research Contributors</h2>\r\n                            <hr>\r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                            <p>Content Here.</p>\r\n                        </article>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n                <section class="post standard">\r\n                    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                        <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                            \r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                            \r\n                        </article>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n                \r\n                <section class="post standard">\r\n                    <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                        <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                            \r\n                        </header>\r\n                        <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                            \r\n                        </article>\r\n                    </div>\r\n                </section>\r\n            </div>     ', 'Contributors', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'contributors', '', '', '2016-02-14 05:30:46', '2016-02-14 05:30:46', '', 0, 'http://localhost/life-measures-wordpress/?page_id=201', 0, 'page', '', 0),
	(203, 1, '2015-03-05 03:04:19', '2015-03-05 03:04:19', '<body id="api-documentation" class="page page-id-128 page-child parent-pageid-17 page-template page-template-page-api-documentation-php win8.1 chrome chrome-0">\r\n<section class="intro-image" style="background-image: url(&#39;<?php echo get_template_directory_uri(); ?>/images/cki-template11-headers-api.jpg&#39;);">\r\n            \r\n            <header>\r\n                <h1>How to Use Our Data API</h1>\r\n                <hr>\r\n            </header>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <div class="row">\r\n        <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Introduction</h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>Before you can access the API data, you will first need to get a registration key that you will need to use on all of your requests. <a href="<?php echo home_url(); ?>/api-registration">Click here</a> to get your registration key.</p>\r\n                    <p>To gain access to raw information regarding the locations, dimensions, components, and scores affiliated with each Measure (U.S. Measurements or World Measurements), please use one of the following URL use cases.</p>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Resources</h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <table>\r\n                        <tbody>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <th>Resources</th>\r\n                                <th>Description</th>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/locations/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Locations</strong><br>\r\n                                        Returns a list of all states or nations included in the Quality of Life Measures.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/dimensionlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Dimensions</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns a list of the dimensions of quality of life measure, which are shared by the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/componentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Components</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns a list of all components (and their parent dimensions) included in the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/subcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Sub-Components</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns a list of all sub-components (and their parent components) included in the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/subsubcomponentlist/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Sub-Sub-Components</strong>\r\n                                    <br>\r\n                                    Returns a list of all sub-sub-components (and their parent sub-components) included in the U.S. and World Measurements.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                        </tbody>\r\n                    </table>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Scores</h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <table>\r\n                        <tbody>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <th>Scores</th>\r\n                                <th>Description</th>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/summary/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p></td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Summary Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns all states or nations, scores and rankings related with the Quality of Life Measures for the most recent year that we have data.</td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>All Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                        Returns all states or nations, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, scores and rankings related with the Quality of Life Measures. Includes historical data back to 2001 for US data, and 2000 for World data.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/dimensions/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Dimension Scores</strong>\r\n                                    <br>\r\n                                    Returns all dimension scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.</td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/components/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Component Scores</strong>\r\n                                    Returns all component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/subcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <strong>Sub-Component Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns all sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <h4>U.S.</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <h4>World</h4>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/int/subsubcomponents/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                </td>\r\n                                <td><strong>Sub-Sub-Component Scores</strong><br>\r\n                                    Returns all sub-sub-component scores from all states or nations (and from all years) included in the Measure.\r\n                                </td>\r\n                            </tr>\r\n                        </tbody>\r\n                    </table>\r\n                </article>\r\n            </div>\r\n        </section>\r\n        <section class="post standard">\r\n            <div class="row clearfix">\r\n                <header class="large-3 medium-3 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <h2>Targeted Queries</h2>\r\n                    <hr>\r\n                </header>\r\n                <article class="large-8 large-offset-1 medium-8 medium-offset-1 small-12 columns">\r\n                    <p>Generating targeted lists of specific data points is done by adding query parameters to your URL. This can allow you to specify your search criteria (ex.; locations, years, dimensions, components, etc.) and get a detailed object of that data as well as a calculated score and ranking based on the returned data.</p>\r\n                    <h3>Base URLs</h3>\r\n                    <table>\r\n                        <tbody>\r\n                            <tr>\r\n                                <td>U.S.</td>\r\n                                <td>\r\n                                    <p>http://life-measures-wordpress.wdoitsolutions.com/api/index.php/us/scores/?key=yourRegistrationKey</p>\r\n                                    <p>This call will return all states, dimensions, components, subcomponents, sub-sub-components, and all of the scores related to the Quality of Life U.S. Measurements. Includes historical data back to 2001.\r\n                                    </p>\r\n                                </